rticle researching the relationship between technology and literacy education phd university of wisconsin madison 1969 ma university of wisconsin madison 1967 ba tulane university 1964 time at stanford since 1996 visiting professor 1996 1997 consulting professor 1997 professional experience faculty associate university of texas 1969 1971 faculty associate and director of reading clinic arizona state university 1971 1972 assistant professor of psychology university of minnesota duluth 1972 1974 assistant professor of education and director of reading clinic purdue university 1978 1980 associate professor of education university of illinois chicago 1980 1989 visiting professor educational theory & practice ohio state university 1989 1990 associate professor educational theory & practice ohio state university 1990 1992 professor educational theory & practice ohio state university 1992 1996 courses taught reading in a second language ed 364x trends and issues in reading ed 366x reading research syntheses policy and practice ed 367x trends and issues in reading ed 480 recent publications handbook of reading research volume iii with p mosenthal pd pearson & r barr 2000 professional development for teaching reading with d strickland 2004 successful reading instruction with h walberg & j manning 2002 kamil ml 2004 the current state of quantitative research reading research quarterly current activities member national literacy panel for language minority children 2002 member editorial advisory board journal of educational psychology 2003 member rand reading study group 2000 2003 member national institute of child health and development national reading panel 1998 2000 faculty &amp research faculty profiles faculty research interests faculty centers suse faculty open positions suse open archive proposal and research resources resources for faculty login stanford university school of education 485 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 3096 tel 650 723 2109 copyright 2012 stanford univ